This paper proposes a single target tracking algorithm that uses deep learning techniques such as Region Proposal Network and Generative Adversarial Networks. The paper focuses on solving the problem of occlusion in single target tracking, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques such as GANs, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence research, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm, which suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of motion trajectory prediction, which is relevant to robotics, so cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on a dataset, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
